properties.Name: CreditScoringModelScoreRange
properties.Description:
The meaning assigned to ranges of credit scores for the applicable credit scoring model. Some scoring models will have both a grade and a description while others may only have one or the other.

Ex.:

800-850 - Excellent
700-799 - Very Good
680-699 - Good
620-679 - Fair
580-619 - Poor
500-579 - Bad
0-499 - Very Bad

901-990 - A - Super prime
801-900 - B - Prime plus
701-800 - C - Prime
601-700 - D - Nonprime
501-600 - F - High risk

Columns.Name: CreditScoringModelId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Credit Scoring Model.

Columns.Name: CreditScoringModelMinimumCreditScore
Columns.Description: The minimum credit score for which this description describes the credit score.

Columns.Name: CreditScoringModelMaximumCreditScore
Columns.Description: The maximum credit score for which this description describes the credit score.

Columns.Name: CreditScoringModelScoreRangeGrade
Columns.Description: The grade assigned to the range of credit scores.

Columns.Name: CreditScoringModelScoreRangeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of a Credit Scoring Model Score Range.
